The NICAR Hitchhiker's Guide To Web APIs is a guide for journalists who want to learn how to use web APIs to get data for their reporting. The guide covers the basics of APIs, how to use Postman to explore an API, and how to get data from the Chicago crime data API.

The guide is written in a clear and concise style, and it includes plenty of screenshots and examples to help readers understand the concepts. The guide is also well-organized, with each section building on the previous one.

Overall, the NICAR Hitchhiker's Guide To Web APIs is a valuable resource for journalists who want to learn how to use web APIs. The guide is well-written and easy to follow, and it includes plenty of examples and screenshots. I highly recommend it to anyone who wants to learn more about web APIs.

